🎅 You’ll never believe what Santa brought us this year! (We couldn’t either)

Merry Christmas from the soon-to-be 4 Daltons! Baby sister is coming April 2023!

Eddie has been less than excited and frequently says “no baby” (see video). However, mom and dad couldn’t be more happy about it!

We have so much to be thankful for this Christmas, especially the miracle and gift of another precious life upon us! God is good.

Merry Christmas to you and yours! ❤️ 

#MerryChristmas #Christmas2022 #TeamBabyDalton #TheDreamChasingFamily #AllThingsAdventure

The romance of life I’ve grown to appreciate most consists of the seemingly simple but diligent day to day efforts of my dear wife Sarah that collectively amount to my whole world.

Thanks for being my consistent companion, the most incredible mother, and making even the mundane meaningful for Eddie and I!

#HappyValentinesDay @sdaltondesign ♥️

10 years is a long time, but not with you. Thanks for putting up with my many flaws. You have been the greatest thing that ever happened to me, and I’m certain always will be. Love you long time!

Happy #10yearanniversary @sdaltondesign! ♥️ xoxo

This weekend we celebrated 10 years of marriage with a short staycation. Eddie got to try his little feet at snowboarding for the first time and surprised us how quick he picked it up! He is getting very brave and curious. We are grateful to be his parents and have each other. Here is to many more years of marriage and parenthood. 🥂

Ready or not, here she comes! T-minus 4 weeks until “baby sister” arrives!

After canceling Sarah’s baby shower for Eddie during the pandemic, she got a proper celebration for this cutie surrounded by family, friends, and delicious food.

Thank you everyone for the love and support! We feel so fortunate that IVF worked again, and are beyond excited to meet our newest family member!

Our little boy is going to be a big brother!

We celebrated Eddie’s last evening as the only child riding bikes with his favorite new @kidsrideshotgun dinosaur bike jersey!

I wish we could freeze time! Where does it go? For too long we battled infertility, and now we are going to have two IVF miracles!

Becoming parents has been our holy grail achievement in life, and I’m convinced always will be.

#EADVII #Utah #MountainBiking #TeamBabyDalton #AllThingsAdventure #TheDreamChasingFamily #Infertility #IVF #Parenthood #DirtHero #ShredTilBed

How we love our lady Luella Elizabeth Dalton!

Our little egg hatched just in time for spring on 4.17.2023 at 02:34 pm. She weighed all of 7 lbs 1 oz, and measured 20 inches. As you can see, both Mom and Luella are doing wonderfully.

It’s hard to put into words the large spectrum of emotions that surface during pregnancy, through delivery, and after coming home with a new family member.

First of all, we are so grateful to have become pregnant, again! It’s no secret that we battled infertility for years. So many of you thoughtfully contributed donations to our #TeamBabyDalton cause that made it financially possible to seek IVF treatment, which finally gave us our first miracle baby Eddie, and now a second — precious Luella! Thank you for supporting our ultimate dream to grow a family.

Also, thank you to the extremely knowledgeable doctors and staff @UtahFertilityCenter. They have been wonderful to work with throughout the daunting IVF treatment process.

Then there is our remarkable OBGYN @docwatts_, who delivered Eddie and started caring for Sarah and Luella before a tragic spinal cord injury. Even though he could not continue practicing, his recovery story has been an inspiration to us of God’s goodness. We adore him, and send his sweet family our love and prayers as he continues to improve.

Thank you to his many friends at @stmarkshospital who filled his big companionate shoes and continued caring for us. Dr. Johnson and the labor and delivery staff were so nice. Healthcare workers are saints.

It would be difficult to overstate how graceful and positive Sarah was from the first of those seemingly endless IVF shots, all the way through childbirth. She is the real MVP here.

There are a very limited number of things that anyone can do to help through the long, involved process of maternity. Sarah always managed to find the beauty of it, while I helplessly worried until hearing that first angelic cry of life.

Luella has quickly shown us the heart’s immense capacity to expand and love without limits. Eddie has adjusted to her arrival with less skepticism than we expected.

We are all so grateful Luella is here!

#TheDreamChasingFamily #AllThingsAdventure

Rush Lake has been (unfortunately) dried up for the last few years from severe drought conditions plaguing the Western US. Fortunately, it is back with a vengeance after a welcome record setting winter.

Rush Lake has rich recreational heritage dating back to at least the early 1980’s. Historically, it was (and still is when filled) notorious as Utah’s own wind sports Mecca!

Thanks to Rush Valley’s overabundance of wind activity and a narrowing funnel effect that accelerates wind speeds, Rush Lake offers up frequent, exceptionally strong winds — perfect for blowing tumble weeds and flying kites!

Here are a few shots from Father’s Day after waiting far too long to ride this nostalgic spot again!

October was a busy, hard, LONG & exhausting month. I felt like I was drowning & barely kept my head above water to breathe. Family pictures were also in October. I didn’t make time to get my hair done (or Eddie’s trimmed) before pics. Forgot Lue’s shoes at the house & my lil sister told me I needed some lip gloss because my lips were chapped & looked like a butthole, but somehow they still turned out. Mostly because Eddie stole the show 😂

Side note: @abbeykyhl was our wedding photographer 10 years ago & flipped her car on the way home from our reception in a snowstorm. I thought for sure she’d “fire” us after that, but she has let us stick around ❤️
Trying to find the “perfect” Christmas tree is harder now with two littles tagging along, but we wouldn’t have it any other way ❤️.

🌺 We enjoyed a (mostly) wonderful trip to Hawaii this year to celebrate the holidays. Contracting RSV (presumably from the flights) was the hefty price to pay for an Aloha Christmas!

Between the sleepless nights up with the sick keikis (Hawaiian for kiddos) and roadside pit stops to clean up car seat puke, we found some Mele Kalikimaka (Merry Christmas) along the Kamehameha Highway of Oahu’s North Shore! Now that we are recuperated, here are some of the trip highlights — and the first video I’ve found time to make since Luella’s birth!

We enjoyed our island time: watching some sunrises (mostly because we were already awake with sickies so why not), playing in the sand (and eating it by the fist fulls if your name is Luella), Waimea Bay surfing, waterfall hikes, cliff jumping, hammocking beneath palm trees, *mostly* casual conversation and laughter with family (only few tiffs), slow scenic drives listening to this song on repeat per Eddie’s request (IYKYK), sightseeing beautiful temples, some kiteboarding (Cody’s favorite), wildlife encounters (feeding fishes, holding birds, catching frogs, and snorkeling with fish and sea turtles), sandy feet beach walks, volleyball, good good food, PCC luau overdose on slow-cooked imu Kalua pork, Hula dancing, Dole Whips on the Pineapple Express, and did I mention that Eddie stopped using a diaper for going #2, and hasn’t turned back since!? He is still working on his ‘Shaka’ hand though! 🤙 

I’m sure I’ve forgotten something else noteworthy, so pictures will probably follow.
